{
  "texts": [
    "By employing the concept of quantum mixed states to establish connections between neighboring words, the contextual information of these associated words can amplify the overall semantic understanding of the input text.",
    "Furthermore, by amalgamating the correlation coefficient among words with the similarity of word vectors and the weight coefficients of PoS, the objective is to accentuate the semantics of frequently used phrases, thereby augmenting the semantic significance of frequently employed PoS combinations.Third, considering the redundant information introduced by dimension expansion in the text representation grounded on density matrix of the correlated words, the pruning conditions of the provided model are formulated by introducing a constraint function rooted in convex optimization theory.",
    "This model optimizes the text representation, meeting the pruning conditions at both the sentence and associated word levels, respectively.The rest of this paper is organized as follows.",
    "Section 2 summarizes some related literature on text representation and semantic similarity.",
    "Section 3 explains our proposed quantum-like tensor compression sentence representation model based on constraint functions for semantics analysis in detail."
  ]
}